	<h2>Mission</h2>
	<p>Code for Philly is volunteering 2.0. We create opportunities for citizens to modernize Philadelphia through the power of the web.</p>
	<p>Founded under <a href="http://codeforamerica.org">Code for America's</a> inaugural <a href="http://brigade.codeforamerica.org">Brigade Program</a> in 2012, Code for Philly currently hosts a weekly <a href="http://meetup.com/Code-for-America-Philly/">Meetup</a> and participates in a number of hackathons and web-based City projects.</p>
	<p>Code for Philly is non-partisan and non-political.</p>
	<h2>Who We Are</h2>
	<p>We are an open team of hard-core web geeks, municipal programmers, technology insiders, and social entrepreneurs - A collective of hacker citizenry, dedicated to re-imaginng City government through civic apps.</p> 
	<p>Meet our <a href="http://codeforphilly.org/members">Members</a></p>
	<h2>What We Do</h2>
	<p>Code for Philly is building a network of civic leaders, organizations and startups who believe there is a better way of doing things and want to make a difference. Together, we utilize our unique talents to create new technology that helps Philadelphia work better for everyone. - To learn more about our innovative applications, check out our <a href="http://codeforphilly.org/projects">Projects</a> page.</p>
	<h2>How We Make a Difference</h2>
	<p>Code for Philly helps City government become more connected, lean, and participatory through new opportunities for public service -- both inside and outside government -- so we're not only making a direct impact everyday, but also creating the relationships and network for lasting change.</p>
